{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8a1dd0a9-309e-488f-9945-d2524d80fa2f","content":"In .NET MAUI, you configure platform lifecycle events in `CreateMauiApp()` using `ConfigureLifecycleEvents`:\n\n```csharp\nusing Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;\n\nbuilder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>\n{\n#if ANDROID\n    events.AddAndroid(android => android\n        .OnPause(activity => HandleBackground())\n        .OnStop(activity => HandleBackground()));\n#elif IOS\n    events.AddiOS(ios => ios\n        .DidEnterBackground(app => HandleBackground()));\n#endif\n});\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- Add `using Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;`\n- Use `#if ANDROID` / `#elif IOS` preprocessor directives to keep platform code conditional.\n- **Android:** `OnPause` fires when partially obscured; `OnStop` when fully hidden.\n- **iOS:** `DidEnterBackground` fires when the app is no longer visible.\n- Each handler receives the platform-native object (`Activity` on Android, `UIApplication` on iOS).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"04a76b2b-74ce-4e82-8679-09a56fc96549","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to hook into platform-specific lifecycle events in .NET MAUI — specifically Android's `OnPause`/`OnStop` and iOS's `DidEnterBackground`. This is a knowledge question, not a code task in the repository.","outputTokens":337,"requestId":"1037:1F16:13E5E97:165E83E:69FD343F"},"id":"fff27b4b-8caf-455f-932e-feac209626b7","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:54:32.299Z","parentId":"6520e686-2c49-4f41-a819-1f7ff28c060f"}
